                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13156313" author="owulff" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2011 21:45:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Had to add support for the RST lifetime element in DefaultConditionsProvider to create testcase&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156784" author="coheigea" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 16:13:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Oli,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks good apart from the change to DefaultConditionsProvider - the change means that the STS will issue tokens by default with the conditions requested by the client...potentially a security concern. Maybe we could make this behaviour pluggable or something.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Colm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13156787" author="owulff" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 16:16:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Colm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agreed. I was first thinking in adding a parameter like &quot;maxLifetime&quot; with a meaningful default like (1 hour). I thought I didn&apos;t want to make too many changes but it really makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What do you think?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oli&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158542" author="coheigea" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 16:34:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Oli,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yep that sounds good. I would also add a boolean whether to accept client lifetime requests at all (defaults to false).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Colm.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158864" author="owulff" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 22:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;acceptClientLifetime added&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
